\begin_layout Section*
Solving the Second-Stage MILP using MATLAB
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We now want to solve the second-stage MILP where we fix 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=\alpha^{\mathrm{opt}}$
\end_inset

.
 Thus the second-stage MILP has the form:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\text{minimize} & \quad E\nonumber \\
\text{subject to} & \quad\alpha\leq D\nonumber \\
 & \quad-\alpha\leq D\nonumber \\
 & \quad\sum_{i=1}^{N}b_{i}v_{i}x_{i}-1\leq E\nonumber \\
 & \quad1-\sum_{i=1}^{N}b_{i}v_{i}x_{i}\leq E\label{eq:MILP1-1}\\
 & \quad\varepsilon_{i}z_{i}\leq(V_{i,T}/C)x_{i}\leq\delta_{i}z_{i} & 1\leq i\leq N\nonumber \\
 & \quad\sum_{i=1}^{N}v_{i}x_{i}=1\nonumber \\
 & \quad\sum_{i=1}^{N}z_{i}=K\nonumber \\
 & \quad x_{i},D,E\geq0 & 1\leq i\leq N\nonumber \\
 & \quad z_{i}\in\{0,1\} & 1\leq i\leq N\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset

To solve this MILP, we only need to make a few changes to the code already
 introduced above.
 In particular, we create a MATLAB function denoted 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

function [x,beta] = MinimizeBeta(I, V, X, cash, gamma, epsilon, delta, K,
 alpha)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 whose code is given below.
 This function solves the MILP 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{eq:MILP2})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and returns the optimal solution 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{x}$
\end_inset

 together with together with 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=\beta^{\mathrm{opt}}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Tabular
<lyxtabular version="3" rows="1" columns="1">
